The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Gopi back with a bang

Hyderabad: Former All-England champion Pullela Gopichand made an emphatic return to the court as he eased past compatriot Rituparna Kulkarni in the first round of the $10,000 Asian Satellite badminton meet here on Monday. 

Gopichand, out of action for over eight months owing to a knee-injury, showed no signs of strain or pressure to brush aside Kulkarni 15-5, 15-4 at the Gachibowli Indoor Stadium. 

Top seed Abhinn Shyam Gupta lived up to his billing as he trounced F. Maserzadeh of Iran 15-4, 15-1 while national champion Chetan Anand moved into the next round defeating D. Karunaratanee of Sri Lanka 15-11, 15-2. 

In men?s doubles, Indian pair Marcos Bristow and Jaison Xavier got the better of Wajid Ali and Omar Zeeshan of Pakistan 15-5, 15-6. Among women, Krishna Deka Raja tamed Thilini Jayasinghee 11-7, 11-6. (PTI) 

